/*Create a class named Rectangle. In the body of the class
create two fields describing the lengths of the sides double side1, double side2. Create two methods,
Calculating the area of a rectangle â€“ double areaCalculator (double side1, double side2) and perimeter
rectangle - double perimeterCalculator (double side1, double side2). Write a program that
accepts the length of two sides of a rectangle from the user and displays the perimeter and
square.*/

import java.util.Scanner;

public class Rectangle {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("enter side1: ");
        double side1 = sc.nextDouble();;
        System.out.print("enter side2: ");
        double side2 = sc.nextDouble();

        System.out.println("area " + perimeterCalculator(side1,side2));
        System.out.println("perimetr " + areaCalculator(side1,side2));
    }

    public static double  areaCalculator (double side1, double side2){
        return side1*side2;
    }

    public static double perimeterCalculator (double side1, double side2){
        return (2*(side1+side2));
    }
}

